description: This object controls the redundancy mode of the load balancer device itself.
When set to none, no redundant load balancer is used.
When set to activeActive, then two load balancers are used, a primary and a secondary.
Both are considered to be active in that both receive network traffic, but one is the designated
primary and one is the designated secondary. Details of primary and secondary behavior
are outside the scope of this MIB.
When set to activeStandby, then two load balancers are used, a primary and a secondary.
One is considered to be active and one is considered to be in standby.
Details of primary and secondary behavior are outside the scope of this MIB.
When this objects is not set to none, the haPort must be set to the
sensor port number which is used to interconnect two devices.
The sensor ports are numbered 1..8 corresponding to device physical ports 17..24.
variables.name: NETOPTICS-XFAM-HA-MIB::haConfigMode

variables.name: NETOPTICS-XFAM-HA-MIB::haConfigSyncStatus

description: The ID taken from the source of the last configuration which was synchronized to.
If this device was the source of the sync (i.e. was pushed to peer device) then it will
be identical to the haLastConfigCommitID on this device as
used for the config sync operation. If the source
was the peer device, then this ID will be identical to the value of both
haLastConfigCommitID and haLastConfigSyncID
on the peer device. This value begins at zero and increases monotonically.
variables.name: NETOPTICS-XFAM-HA-MIB::haLastConfigSyncID

description: The source of the last configuration sync or resync, either
self or the peer device.
variables.name: NETOPTICS-XFAM-HA-MIB::haLastConfigSyncSource

description: The date and time taken from the source of the last configuration which was synchronized to.
If this device was the source of the sync (i.e. was pushed to peer device) then it will
be identical to the haLastConfigCommitTime on this device as
used for the config sync operation. If the source
was the peer device, then this time will be identical to the value of both
haLastConfigCommitTime and haLastConfigSyncTime
on the peer device. Value is a string date and time in the devices' local time zone.
variables.name: NETOPTICS-XFAM-HA-MIB::haLastConfigSyncTime

description: An ID which increments each time the ha configuration subset is committed on this device.
This subset comprises those objects which are synchronized between HA peers.
It does NOT include objects used to configure HA operation itself such as the haConfig objects in this MIB.
variables.name: NETOPTICS-XFAM-HA-MIB::haLastConfigCommitID

description: High-Availability Last Synchronized Commit ID, the ID of the local configuration resulting from the last ha config sync.
variables.name: NETOPTICS-XFAM-HA-MIB::haLastConfigSyncCommitID

description: High-Availability count of commits waiting to be synchronized.
The number of local commits to the ha config which have not yet been synchronized with the peer.
This is the difference between haLastConfigCommitID and haLastConfigSyncCommitID.
variables.name: NETOPTICS-XFAM-HA-MIB::haUnsynchronizedCommitCount

description: Sent when a service-affecting configuration mismatch is
detected between the Primary and Secondary HA peers. For example, if the
LBG settings differ between the peers then normal HA operation cannot be carried out.

Summary.eval: ($v3==0) ? 'HA configuration mismatch error cleared' : 'HA configuration mismatch error occurred'
